        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 21 at 9:30PM CDT by NWS Aberdeen SD</headline>
        <description>At 930 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Memorial Park Camping Site to Kranzburg to
Moritz. Movement was south at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Watertown, Clear Lake, Goose Lake, Rauville, Gary, Waverly,
Kranzburg, Goodwin, Revillo, Strandburg, La Bolt, Troy, Altamont,
Albee, Bemis, Bullhead Lake, Moritz, Lake Kampeska, Watertown City
Park, and Dakota Sioux Casino.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
